The paper discusses a neural-based method for automatic question generation, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The paper also mentions applications such as question answering systems and dialogue systems, which are relevant to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and language and information processing (cs.LG). The paper also uses a discriminator to capture relations between the passage and the answer, which is a common technique in neural networks for natural language processing and machine learning, relevant to sub-categories such as neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
